Header.Info: Performance Monitoring Events for Intel(R) Core(TM) Ultra series 3 processors (codenamed Panther Lake) - V1.03

Events.BriefDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of instructions retired.
Events.PublicDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of instructions retired.

Events.BriefDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of unhalted core clock cycles.
Events.PublicDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of unhalted core clock cycles.

Events.BriefDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of unhalted core clock cycles.
Events.PublicDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of unhalted core clock cycles.

Events.BriefDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of unhalted reference clock cycles.
Events.PublicDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of unhalted reference clock cycles.

Events.BriefDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of issue slots that were not consumed by the backend because allocation is stalled due to a mispredicted jump or a machine clear.
Events.PublicDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of issue slots that were not consumed by the backend because allocation is stalled due to a mispredicted jump or a machine clear.

Events.BriefDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of retirement slots not consumed due to front end stalls.
Events.PublicDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of retirement slots not consumed due to front end stalls.

Events.BriefDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of consumed retirement slots.
Events.PublicDescription: Fixed Counter: Counts the number of consumed retirement slots.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of retired loads that are blocked because its address exactly matches an older store whose data is not ready.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of retired loads that are blocked because its address exactly matches an older store whose data is not ready.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of retired loads that are blocked because its address partially overlapped with an older store.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of retired loads that are blocked because its address partially overlapped with an older store.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of retired loads that are blocked because it initially appears to be store forward blocked, but subsequently is shown not to be blocked based on 4K alias check.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of retired loads that are blocked because it initially appears to be store forward blocked, but subsequently is shown not to be blocked based on 4K alias check.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of retired loads that are blocked due to a first level TLB miss.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of retired loads that are blocked due to a first level TLB miss.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of retired loads that are blocked for any of the following reasons:  DTLB miss, address alias, store forward or data unknown (includes memory disambiguation blocks and ESP consuming load blocks).
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of retired loads that are blocked for any of the following reasons:  DTLB miss, address alias, store forward or data unknown (includes memory disambiguation blocks and ESP consuming load blocks).

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked due to a store buffer full condition.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked due to a store buffer full condition.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked due to a load buffer full condition.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked due to a load buffer full condition.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked due to an RSV full condition.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked due to an RSV full condition.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked for any of the following reasons:  load buffer, store buffer or RSV full.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked for any of the following reasons:  load buffer, store buffer or RSV full.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles that the head (oldest load) of the load buffer is stalled due to a DL1 miss.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles that the head (oldest load) of the load buffer is stalled due to a DL1 miss.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles that the head (oldest load) of the load buffer is stalled due to request buffers full or lock in progress.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles that the head (oldest load) of the load buffer is stalled due to request buffers full or lock in progress.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles that the head (oldest load) of the load buffer and retirement are both stalled due to a DL1 miss.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles that the head (oldest load) of the load buffer and retirement are both stalled due to a DL1 miss.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles that the head (oldest load) of the load buffer and retirement are both stalled due to request buffers full or lock in progress.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles that the head (oldest load) of the load buffer and retirement are both stalled due to request buffers full or lock in progress.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles that the head (oldest load) of the load buffer is stalled due to a core bound stall including a store address match, a DTLB miss or a page walk that detains the load from retiring.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles that the head (oldest load) of the load buffer is stalled due to a core bound stall including a store address match, a DTLB miss or a page walk that detains the load from retiring.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of page walks initiated by a demand load that missed the first and second level TLBs.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of page walks initiated by a demand load that missed the first and second level TLBs.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to load DTLB misses to a 4K page.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to loads (including SW prefetches) whose address translations missed in all Translation Lookaside Buffer (TLB) levels and were mapped to 4K pages. Includes page walks that page fault.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to load DTLB misses to any page size.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to loads (including SW prefetches) whose address translations missed in all Translation Lookaside Buffer (TLB) levels and were mapped to any page size. Includes page walks that page fault.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of first level TLB misses but second level hits due to a demand load that did not start a page walk. Accounts for all page sizes. Will result in a DTLB write from STLB.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of first level TLB misses but second level hits due to a demand load that did not start a page walk. Accounts for all page sizes. Will result in a DTLB write from STLB.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops issued by the front end every cycle.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops issued by the front end every cycle. When 4-uops are requested and only 2-uops are delivered, the event counts 2. Uops_issued correlates to the number of ROB entries. If uop takes 2 ROB slots it counts as 2 uops_issued.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts misaligned loads that are 4K page splits.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts misaligned loads that are 4K page splits.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts misaligned stores that are 4K page splits.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts misaligned stores that are 4K page splits.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand Data Read requests that resulted in a Miss. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand Data Read requests that resulted in a Miss. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand RFO requests that resulted in a Miss. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand RFO requests that resulted in a Miss. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand Code Read requests that resulted in a Miss. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand Code Read requests that resulted in a Miss. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door requests that resulted in a Miss. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door requests that resulted in a Miss. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door requests that resulted in a Hit. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door requests that resulted in a Hit. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand Data Read requests. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand Data Read requests. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand RFO requests. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand RFO requests. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand Code Read requests. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door Demand Code Read requests. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door requests for Code Read, Data Read, RFO, ITOM, and L2 Prefetches. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of L2 cache accesses from front door requests for Code Read, Data Read, RFO, ITOM, and L2 Prefetches. Does not include rejects or recycles, per core event.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cache lines filled into the L2 cache that are in Exclusive state
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cache lines filled into the L2 cache that are in Exclusive state. Counts on a per core basis.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cacheable memory requests that miss in the LLC. Counts on a per core basis.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cacheable memory requests that miss in the Last Level Cache (LLC). Requests include demand loads, reads for ownership (RFO), instruction fetches and L1 HW prefetches. If the core has access to an L3 cache, the LLC is the L3 cache, otherwise it is the L2 cache. Counts on a per core basis.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cacheable memory requests that access the LLC. Counts on a per core basis.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cacheable memory requests that access the Last Level Cache (LLC). Requests include demand loads, reads for ownership (RFO), instruction fetches and L1 HW prefetches. If the core has access to an L3 cache, the LLC is the L3 cache, otherwise it is the L2 cache. Counts on a per core basis.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles the core is stalled due to a demand load which hit in the L2 cache.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles a core is stalled due to a demand load which hit in the L2 cache.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which hit in the LLC, no snoop was required. LLC provided data.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which hit in the LLC, no snoop was required. LLC provided data.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which hit in the LLC, a snoop was required, the snoop misses  or the snoop hits but no fwd. LLC provides the data.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which hit in the LLC, a snoop was required, the snoop misses  or the snoop hits but no fwd. LLC provides the data.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which hit in the LLC.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which hit in the LLC.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which missed all the caches, a snoop was required, and hits in other core or module on same die.  Another core provides the data with a fwd, no fwd, or hitM.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which missed all the caches, a snoop was required, and hits in other core or module on same die.  Another core provides the data with a fwd, no fwd, or hitM.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which missed all the caches.  DRAM, MMIO or other LOCAL memory type provides the data.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which missed all the caches.  DRAM, MMIO or other LOCAL memory type provides the data.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which missed all the local caches.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which missed all the local caches.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of cycles the core is stalled due to a demand load which hit in the L2 cache.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of cycles the core is stalled due to a demand load which hit in the L2 cache.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to an L1 demand load miss.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to an L1 demand load miss.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted core clock cycles. [This event is alias to CPU_CLK_UNHALTED.THREAD_P]
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted core clock cycles. [This event is alias to CPU_CLK_UNHALTED.THREAD_P]

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted core clock cycles. [This event is alias to CPU_CLK_UNHALTED.CORE_P]
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted core clock cycles. [This event is alias to CPU_CLK_UNHALTED.CORE_P]

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted reference clock cycles at TSC frequency.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of reference cycles that the core is not in a halt state. The core enters the halt state when it is running the HLT instruction. This event is not affected by core frequency changes and increments at a fixed frequency that is also used for the Time Stamp Counter (TSC). This event uses a programmable general purpose performance counter.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of page walks initiated by a store that missed the first and second level TLBs.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of page walks initiated by a store that missed the first and second level TLBs.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to store DTLB misses to a 4K page.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to stores whose address translations missed in all Translation Lookaside Buffer (TLB) levels and were mapped to 4K pages.  Includes page walks that page fault.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to store DTLB misses to any page size.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to stores whose address translations missed in all Translation Lookaside Buffer (TLB) levels and were mapped to any page size.  Includes page walks that page fault.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of first level TLB misses but second level hits due to stores that did not start a page walk. Accounts for all page sizes. Will result in a DTLB write from STLB.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of first level TLB misses but second level hits due to a demand load that did not start a page walk. Accounts for all page sizes. Will result in a DTLB write from STLB.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to ms
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to ms

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to BAClear
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to BAClear

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to predecode wrong
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to predecode wrong

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to decode stall
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to decode stall

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to itlb miss
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to itlb miss

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to an icache miss
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to an icache miss

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to BTClear
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to BTClear

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to latency related stalls including BACLEARs, BTCLEARs, ITLB misses, and ICache misses.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to latency related stalls including BACLEARs, BTCLEARs, ITLB misses, and ICache misses.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend that do not categorize into any other common frontend stall
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend that do not categorize into any other common frontend stall

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots that were not consumed by the backend because allocation is stalled due to a mispredicted jump or a machine clear.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the total number of issue slots that were not consumed by the backend because allocation is stalled due to a mispredicted jump or a machine clear. Only issue slots wasted due to fast nukes such as memory ordering nukes are counted. Other nukes are not accounted for. Counts all issue slots blocked during this recovery window, including relevant microcode flows, and while uops are not yet available in the instruction queue (IQ) or until an FE_BOUND event occurs besides OTHER and CISC. Also includes the issue slots that were consumed by the backend but were thrown away because they were younger than the mispredict or machine clear.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to a machine clear (nuke).
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to a machine clear (nuke).

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to Fast Nukes such as  Memory Ordering Machine clears and MRN nukes
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to Fast Nukes such as  Memory Ordering Machine clears and MRN nukes

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the total number of issue slots that were not consumed by the backend because allocation is stalled due to a machine clear (nuke) of any kind including memory ordering and memory disambiguation.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the total number of issue slots that were not consumed by the backend because allocation is stalled due to a machine clear (nuke) of any kind including memory ordering and memory disambiguation.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to Branch Mispredict
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to Branch Mispredict

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to a branch mispredict that resulted in LSD exit.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to a branch mispredict that resulted in LSD exit.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to due to certain allocation restrictions.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to due to certain allocation restrictions.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to memory reservation stall (scheduler not being able to accept another uop).  This could be caused by RSV full or load/store buffer block.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to memory reservation stall (scheduler not being able to accept another uop).  This could be caused by RSV full or load/store buffer block.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to iq/jeu scoreboards or ms scb
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to iq/jeu scoreboards or ms scb

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to ROB full
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to ROB full

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to LSD entry.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not consumed by the backend due to LSD entry.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots where no uop could issue due to an IQ scoreboard that stalls allocation until a specified older uop retires or (in the case of jump scoreboard) executes. Commonly executed instructions with IQ scoreboards include LFENCE and MFENCE.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots where no uop could issue due to an IQ scoreboard that stalls allocation until a specified older uop retires or (in the case of jump scoreboard) executes. Commonly executed instructions with IQ scoreboards include LFENCE and MFENCE.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots not consumed by the backend due to a micro-sequencer (MS) scoreboard, which stalls the front-end from issuing from the UROM until a specified older uop retires.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots not consumed by the backend due to a micro-sequencer (MS) scoreboard, which stalls the front-end from issuing from the UROM until a specified older uop retires. The most commonly executed instruction with an MS scoreboard is PAUSE.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of issue slots in a UMWAIT or TPAUSE instruction where no uop issues due to the instruction putting the CPU into the C0.1 activity state. For Tremont, UMWAIT and TPAUSE will only put the CPU into C0.1 activity state (not C0.2 activity state).
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of issue slots in a UMWAIT or TPAUSE instruction where no uop issues due to the instruction putting the CPU into the C0.1 activity state. For Tremont, UMWAIT and TPAUSE will only put the CPU into C0.1 activity state (not C0.2 activity state).

Events.BriefDescription: Counts every time the code stream enters into a new cache line by walking sequential from the previous line or being redirected by a jump and the instruction cache registers bytes are present.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts every time the code stream enters into a new cache line by walking sequential from the previous line or being redirected by a jump and the instruction cache registers bytes are present.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts every time the code stream enters into a new cache line by walking sequential from the previous line or being redirected by a jump and the instruction cache registers bytes are not present. -
Events.PublicDescription: Counts every time the code stream enters into a new cache line by walking sequential from the previous line or being redirected by a jump and the instruction cache registers bytes are not present. -

Events.BriefDescription: Counts every time the code stream enters into a new cache line by walking sequential from the previous line or being redirected by a jump.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts every time the code stream enters into a new cache line by walking sequential from the previous line or being redirected by a jump.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of page walks initiated by a instruction fetch that missed the first and second level TLBs.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of page walks initiated by a instruction fetch that missed the first and second level TLBs.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to instruction fetch misses to a 4K page.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to instruction fetches whose address translations missed in all Translation Lookaside Buffer (TLB) levels and were mapped to 4K pages.  Includes page walks that page fault.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to instruction fetch misses to any page size.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of page walks completed due to instruction fetches whose address translations missed in all Translation Lookaside Buffer (TLB) levels and were mapped to any page size.  Includes page walks that page fault.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of page walks outstanding for iside in PMH every cycle.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of page walks outstanding for iside in PMH every cycle.  A PMH page walk is outstanding from page walk start till PMH becomes idle again (ready to serve next walk). Includes EPT-walk intervals.  Walks could be counted by edge detecting on this event, but would count restarted suspended walks.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of first level TLB misses but second level hits due to an instruction fetch that did not start a page walk. Account for all pages sizes. Will result in an ITLB write from STLB.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of first level TLB misses but second level hits due to an instruction fetch that did not start a page walk. Account for all pages sizes. Will result in an ITLB write from STLB.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of retirement slots not consumed due to front end stalls.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of retirement slots not consumed due to front end stalls.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of retirement slots not consumed due to backend stalls. [This event is alias to TOPDOWN_BE_BOUND.ALL]
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of retirement slots not consumed due to backend stalls. [This event is alias to TOPDOWN_BE_BOUND.ALL]

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of retirement slots not consumed due to backend stalls. [This event is alias to TOPDOWN_BE_BOUND.ALL_P]
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of retirement slots not consumed due to backend stalls. [This event is alias to TOPDOWN_BE_BOUND.ALL_P]

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer store data port.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer store data port.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer port 0.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer port 0.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer port 1.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer port 1.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer port 2.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer port 2.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer port 3.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer port 3.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer port 0, 1, 2, 3.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on floating point and vector integer port 0, 1, 2, 3.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on all floating point ports.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on all floating point ports.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on a load port.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on a load port.  This event counts for integer uops even if the destination is FP/vector

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on a Store address port.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on a Store address port. This event counts integer uops even if the data source is FP/vector

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on an integer store data and jump port.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on an integer store data and jump port.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 0.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 0.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 1.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 1.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 2.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 2.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 3.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 3.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port  0,1, 2, 3.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port  0,1, 2, 3.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on secondary integer ports 0,1,2,3.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on secondary integer ports 0,1,2,3.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on all Integer ports.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on all Integer ports.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts demand data reads that have any type of response.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts demand data reads that have any type of response.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts demand data reads that were supplied by DRAM.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts demand data reads that were supplied by DRAM.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts demand data reads that were not supplied by the L3 cache.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts demand data reads that were not supplied by the L3 cache.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts demand read for ownership (RFO) requests and software prefetches for exclusive ownership (PREFETCHW) that have any type of response.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts demand read for ownership (RFO) requests and software prefetches for exclusive ownership (PREFETCHW) that have any type of response.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts demand read for ownership (RFO) requests and software prefetches for exclusive ownership (PREFETCHW) that were not supplied by the L3 cache.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts demand read for ownership (RFO) requests and software prefetches for exclusive ownership (PREFETCHW) that were not supplied by the L3 cache.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of instructions retired.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of instructions retired.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of x87 uops retired, includes those in ms flows.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of x87 uops retired, includes those in ms flows.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops retired that are the last uop of a macro-instruction.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops retired that are the last uop of a macro-instruction.   EOM uops indicate the 'end of a macro-instruction' and play a crucial role in the processor's control flow and recovery mechanisms.

Events.BriefDescription: Counts the total number of mispredicted branch instructions retired for all branch types.
Events.PublicDescription: Counts the total number of mispredicted branch instructions retired.  All branch type instructions are accounted for.  Prediction of the branch target address enables the processor to begin executing instructions before the non-speculative execution path is known. The branch prediction unit (BPU) predicts the target address based on the instruction pointer (IP) of the branch and on the execution path through which execution reached this IP.    A branch misprediction occurs when the prediction is wrong, and results in discarding all instructions executed in the speculative path and re-fetching from the correct path.
